{{zh-forms|alt=㳄,㵪,唌,㳭,湺,𣵿,𠿢}}
Probably {{der|zh|sit}}; compare {{cog|cvg|har||phlegm}}, {{cog|lsh|hahal||phlegm}}, Rupa {{cog|sdp|nəkʰɔ̃ː||phlegm}}, {{cog|sit-jap|tɯɴɢar||sputum}} ({{zh-ref|Bodt, 2021}}). {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, who reconstructs the {{cog|och|-}} minimally as {{m|und|*(s-)lan}}, compares it to {{cog|bo|tr=zlan|t=moisture}}.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} relates it to {{cog|th|น้ำลาย}}, which is derived from {{cog|tai-pro|*laːjᴬ||saliva}}.

Possibly related to {{och-l|羨|id=2|to envy}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}; also cf. {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}).

